        "vulnStatus": "Analyzed",
        "descriptions": [
          {
            "lang": "en",
            "value": "A flaw was found in the python-cryptography package. This issue may allow a remote attacker to decrypt captured messages in TLS servers that use RSA key exchanges, which may lead to exposure of confidential or sensitive data. This is a variant of the PKCS#1 v1.5 Bleichenbacher timing side-channel attack."
          }
        ],
